full_text: In Contact Manager, the Vendor Manager can add documents and services to a vendor record. When that vendor is used on a claim in ClaimCenter, the attached documents are available on that claim. Any services that are on the vendor, help with search criteria. Carla is the Vendor Manager for Succeed Insurance. She logs into Contact Manager. Bill's Quick Auto Repair has sent Carla two documents that they normally use on all the claims that they service. She wants to add documents that they service. She has sent those documents to the vendor record and starts by searching for Bill's Quick Auto Repair. She clicks Bill's Quick Auto Repair in the search results. Carla wants to see if there are any documents already on the vendor record. Bill's does not have any documents attached. She then clicks New Documents, Upload Documents. ClaimCenter opens a File System Explorer window, from which she can select the files for upload. Carla selects the service order for the vendor record. Carla does not need to know the Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil Fil tab, Carla clicks the edit button to add those services. She locates the inspection, repair category under the auto service type, and clicks auto body, and glass, and towing. With all three of those services selected, Carla saves the changes. Back in Claim Center, Andy is still on the Andrew Williams claim. He is looking at the parties involved, contacts screen, and he wants to see if there are any documents associated with this vendor. There are two documents, a service order form and a service level agreement. These documents are here because Carla added them to the vendor record. They are automatically available to all claims that have bills quick auto repair as a vendor. Andy knows that Mr. Williams may need to have his truck towed, and wants to see if there are any vendors in San Mateo that offer that service. He wants to limit the search to vendors who provide specific services. Andy clicks add to specify services to restrict the search. He clicks towing, and clicks OK. He adds San Mateo as a city, and with the services restricted to towing, he clicks search. He sees that among others, bills quick auto repair provides towing, and is in San Mateo. Bills is returned in the results list because they are in San Mateo, and Carla added towing as a service to the vendor record. Andy logs out of Claim Center. This is the end of the adding documents and services in contact manager demonstration.
